'''Myopericytoma''', also '''glomangiopericytoma''', is a rare perivascular [[soft tissue]] [[tumour]].  It is usually benign and typically in the distal extremities.<ref name=pmid21111282>{{cite journal |author=Zidane A, Arsalane A, Harkat A, ''et al.'' |title=[Myopericytoma: an uncommon chest wall tumor] |language=French |journal=Rev Mal Respir |volume=27 |issue=9 |pages=1089–91 |year=2010 |month=November |pmid=21111282 |doi=10.1016/j.rmr.2010.09.017 |url=}}</ref>

It is thought to overlap with [[myofibroma]].<ref>{{cite journal |author=Dray MS, McCarthy SW, Palmer AA, ''et al.'' |title=Myopericytoma: a unifying term for a spectrum of tumours that show overlapping features with myofibroma. A review of 14 cases |journal=J. Clin. Pathol. |volume=59 |issue=1 |pages=67–73 |year=2006 |month=January |pmid=16394283 |pmc=1860256 |doi=10.1136/jcp.2005.028704 |url=}}</ref>

